steps to create and delete kubernetes cluster using eksctl 

Prerequisites: 

Before starting this tutorial, you must install and configure the AWS CLI, 
kubectl, and eksctl tools in your local computer.

Step 1: Create your Amazon EKS cluster and nodes

You can create a cluster with one of the following node types
Fargate – Linux – Select this type of node if you want to run Linux applications on Simplify compute management with AWS Fargate. Fargate is a serverless compute engine that lets you deploy Kubernetes Pods without managing Amazon EC2 instances.

eksctl create cluster --name my-cluster --region region-code --fargate

Managed nodes – Linux – Select this type of node if you want to run Amazon Linux applications on Amazon EC2 instances. 

eksctl create cluster --name my-cluster --region region-code

eksctl created a kubectl config file in ~/.kube/config or 
added the new cluster’s configuration within an existing config file in ~/.kube/config on your computer.

Step 2: View Kubernetes resources

kubectl get nodes -o wide

Step 3: Delete your cluster and nodes

eksctl delete cluster --name my-cluster --region region-code

